xt) growth <- function(rate, xt) { pob = (rate * xt) * (1 - xt) return(pob) } # Funci贸n recursiva para obtener la poblaci贸n para cada tiempo "t" iterGrowth <- function(xt, rate, t, xinit) { res = NULL if (t == 0) { res = xt return(res) } else if (t == 1) { res = growth(rate = rate, xt = xt) return(res) } else{ i = 1 while (i <= (t)) { res[i + 1] = growth(rate = rate, xt = xt) xt = growth(rate = rate, xt = xt) i = i + 1 } res[1] = xinit return(res) } } ``` ::: ### Funci贸n 2 -
